				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">they shouldn't be pulling almost the entire zone at a time.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Ehh, not many people care about what they &quot;shouldn't&quot; be doing.
<br />

<br />
Case in point, I was leveling an alt in Highkeep, grouped by gobbies. A lvl 4(yes lvl 4) shaman comes in with bot cleric in tow and proceeds to take WR/RR from my group claiming camp rights. Even though we were there for a good 2-3 hours previous, I wouldn't mind another group or PL team to come share the camps. But to bring a lvl 4 toon down to the basement just to PL is ridiculous! And on top of that, he starts running around our camp in GR trying to aggro things to bring down to himself. We complain and he comes back with the good old &quot;theres no camps, first aggro gets the mobs!&quot;
<br />

<br />
So what can we do? Our 2-3 hour long camp just got discredited. Oh well, WR/RR mobs are more exp anyway, lets go get first aggro on those. The little butthead didn't like that idea too much but he doesn't have much room to argue anymore.
<br />

<br />
There are people who just don't care how their play affects those around them. This isn't a Sony issue, its a behavioral one. Theres so many mobs in MM for lvl 20ish crowd that its so very easy to share with someone there for exp. Or even then, why not plop down next to the expers and help them, you will get faction that way as well.
<br />

<br />
The only fault you can attribute to Sony is their lack of accounting for human crappiness.
<br />

<br />
